{"questionId":"2681403","questionHtml":"<p>Find the area of the cross-section of the gutter.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> There are many different ways to dissect the cross-section to determine its area. In all approaches, candidates will need to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>. Award the first three marks for work seen anywhere.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>evidence of using the cosine rule OR sine rule&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>·</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>·</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>w</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>530796</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6977</mn><mo>…</mo></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3488</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>using trig ratios in a right triangle with angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> and side length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6977</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3488</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7179</mn><mo>…</mo></math> from use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>Let the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math> lie on the figure as follows:</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/09b3ff3464e284b326b158b2aecae09a5e86a543.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>(segment <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AHB</mi><mo>=</mo></math>) sector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math> – triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>149</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>76</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>62</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8655</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8944</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>valid approach to find total cross-sectional area (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>sector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math> – triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math> + rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CDBA</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8944</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>w</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8944</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>206</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>977</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math> throughout leads to segment <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>87</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2517</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and cross-sectional area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>87</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2517</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>207</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>179</mn><mo>…</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>trapezium <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOA</mi></math> (= rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOE</mi></math> + triangle EOA)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6977</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>72</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0557</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>valid approach to find total cross-sectional area (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>2 × trapezium <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOA</mi></math> + sector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>72</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0557</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>111</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>149</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>76</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math> leads to area of trapezium&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOA</mi></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>72</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2154</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and cross-sectional area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>430</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>2 × area of trapezium <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOA</mi></math> (= area of rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CDFE</mi></math> + 2 × triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>EOA</mi></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6977</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>81</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2458</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>62</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8655</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>valid approach to find total cross-sectional area (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>2 × trapezium <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOA</mi></math> + sector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>111</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>111</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>149</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>76</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math> leads to 2 × area of trapezium&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CGOA</mi></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>430</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and cross-sectional area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>430</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>area of cross-section <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>293</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>871</mn></math> (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>294</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>430</mn></math> from exact answer)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>294</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp;[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2681403","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the area of the cross-section of the gutter.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}